title: druid + mysql：compatibility problem?
author: neeuq

comments.body: 是的，你可以尝试一下3.2.3版本，我们已经不再替换Connection.

更新了代码，这个应该没问题了，发现代码结构有些变动。补充个问题：
1、是基于什么考虑，把jdbc监控修改了
2、插件包现在放在外面了，是方便增减，都实际部署时感觉集成至一个jar包更方便，纠结了

> 1、是基于什么考虑，把jdbc监控修改了

主要解决的是这种连接校验的问题。除了Druid之外，有些datasource也监测这个。

> 2、插件包现在放在外面了，是方便增减，都实际部署时感觉集成至一个jar包更方便，纠结了

这个我个人认为，增减是主要特性，你只是多了一个`tar`的操作，我觉得没有必要纠结。

另外，因为此问题已解决，我将关闭此问题。

satisfaction_conditions: Solution maintains compatibility with Druid's connection validation mechanism
Works at the framework level without application changes

_classification.category: Can be dockerized without any issue

repository_info.dockerfile:
--- ./apm-collector/apm-collector-boot/docker/Dockerfile ---
FROM openjdk:8u111-jdk

ENV ZK_ADDRESSES=127.0.0.1:2181 \
    ES_CLUSTER_NAME=CollectorDBCluster \
    ES_ADDRESSES=localhost:9300 \
    BIND_HOST=localhost  \
    CLUSTER_BIND_HOST=localhost \
    CLUSTER_BIND_PORT=11800 \
    UI_BIND_HOST=localhost \
    UI_BIND_PORT=12800 \
    GRPC_BIND_PORT=11800 \
    AGENT_SERVER_BIND_PORT=10800 \
    AGENT_STREAM_JETTY_BIND_PORT=12800

ADD skywalking-collector.tar.gz /usr/local
COPY collector-service.sh /usr/local/skywalking-collector/bin
COPY log4j2.xml /usr/local/skywalking-collector/config
COPY application.yml /usr/local/skywalking-collector/config
COPY docker-entrypoint.sh /

RUN chmod +x /usr/local/skywalking-collector/bin/collector-service.sh && chmod +x /docker-entrypoint.sh

EXPOSE 10800
EXPOSE 11800
EXPOSE 12800

ENTRYPOINT ["/docker-entrypoint.sh"]
CMD ["/usr/local/skywalking-collector/bin/collector-service.sh"]



--- ./apm-collector/apm-collector-boot/docker/application.yml ---
cluster:
  zookeeper:
    hostPort: {ZK_ADDRESSES}
    sessionTimeout: 100000
agent_server:
  jetty:
    host: {BIND_HOST}
    port: {AGENT_SERVER_BIND_PORT}
    context_path: /
agent_stream:
  grpc:
    host: {BIND_HOST}
    port: {GRPC_BIND_PORT}
  jetty:
    host: {UI_BIND_HOST}
    port: {UI_BIND_PORT}
    context_path: /
ui:
  jetty:
    host: {UI_BIND_HOST}
    port: {UI_BIND_PORT}
    context_path: /
collector_inside:
  grpc:
    host: {CLUSTER_BIND_HOST}
    port: {CLUSTER_BIND_PORT}
storage:
  elasticsearch:
    cluster_name: {ES_CLUSTER_NAME}
    cluster_transport_sniffer: true
    cluster_nodes: {ES_ADDRESSES}
    index_shards_number: 2
    index_replicas_number: 0



--- ./apm-collector/apm-collector-boot/docker/collector-service.sh ---
#!/usr/bin/env bash

PRG="$0"
PRGDIR=`dirname "$PRG"`
[ -z "$COLLECTOR_HOME" ] && COLLECTOR_HOME=`cd "$PRGDIR/.." >/dev/null; pwd`

CLASSPATH="$COLLECTOR_HOME/config:$CLASSPATH"
for i in "$COLLECTOR_HOME"/libs/*.jar
do
    CLASSPATH="$i:$CLASSPATH"
done

java ${JAVA_OPTS} ${COLLECTOR_OPTIONS} -classpath $CLASSPATH org.skywalking.apm.collector.boot.CollectorBootStartUp

dockerfile:
FROM openjdk:8-jdk

# Install system dependencies
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y git maven && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Clone SkyWalking repository
RUN git clone https://github.com/apache/skywalking.git /skywalking

WORKDIR /skywalking

# Checkout specific commit with the fix
RUN git checkout 7b05beded8733b863d8ece35ef52601d51affd38

# Build project with Java 8 compatibility and skip tests
RUN mvn clean install -DskipTests -Dcheckstyle.skip=true -Dmaven.compile.source=8 -Dmaven.compile.target=8
